``` r
diamond_model<-lm(price~ .,diamonds)
diamond_model1<-diamonds[1:53000,]
diamond_test1<-diamonds[53001:53940,]
diamond_train1<-diamond_model1
```

### Max Correlation obtained

``` r
diamond_model1<-lm(price~ carat+color+clarity+cut,diamond_train1)
pred_using_Linear<-predict(diamond_model1,diamond_test1)
cor(diamond_test1$price,pred_using_Linear)
```

### Normalizing all the fields for predicition using Knn

``` r
normalize <- function(x) {return ((x - min(x)) / ((max(x) - min(x))))}
diamond_n <- as.data.frame(lapply(diamonds[,c(1:6,8:10)], normalize))
diamond_train<-diamond_n[1:53000,]
diamond_test<-diamond_n[53001:53940,]
diamond_train_labels<-diamonds[1:53000,7, drop=TRUE]
diamond_test_labels<-diamonds[53001:53940,7,drop=TRUE]
pred_using_Knn<-knn(train = diamond_train, test = diamond_test, cl=diamond_train_labels, k=230)
```

### For lower Prices, the value of linear becomes negative.

### So the overall prediction of Knn is good.
